5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to crimes and offenses; to amend Section
10 13A-6-21, Code of Alabama 1975; to revise the crime of assault
11 in the second degree.
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
13 Section 1. Section 13A-6-21, Code of Alabama 1975, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 "§13A-6-21
16 (a) A person commits the crime of assault in the second
17 degree if the person does any of the following:
18 (1) With intent to cause serious physical injury to
19 another person, he or she causes serious physical injury to
20 any person.
21 (2) With intent to cause physical injury to another
22 person, he or she causes physical injury to any person by
23 means of a deadly weapon or a dangerous instrument.
24 (3) He or she recklessly causes serious physical injury
25 to another person by means of a deadly weapon or a dangerous
26 instrument.
27 (4)a. With intent to prevent a peace officer, as
28 defined in Section 36-21-60, a detention or correctional
Page 1

defined in Section 36-21-60, a detention or correctional
HB132 Engrossed
29 officer at any municipal or county jail or state penitentiary,
30 emergency medical personnel, a utility worker, or a
31 firefighter from performing a lawful duty, he or she intends
32 to cause physical injury and he or she causes physical injury
33 to any person.
34 b. For the purpose of this subdivision, a person who is
35 a peace officer who is employed or under contract while off
36 duty by a private or public entity is a peace officer
37 performing a lawful duty when the person is working in his or
38 her approved uniform while off duty with the approval of his
39 or her employing law enforcement agency. Provided, however,
40 that nothing Nothing contained in this subdivision shall be
41 deemed or construed as amending, modifying, or extending the
42 classification of a peace officer as off-duty off duty for
43 workers' compensation purposes or any other benefits to which
44 a peace officer may otherwise be entitled to under law when
45 considered on-dutyon duty. Additionally, nothing contained in
46 this subdivision shall be deemed or construed as amending,
47 modifying, or extending the tort liability of any municipality
48 as a result of any action or inaction on the part of an
49 off-duty police officer.
50 (5) With intent to cause physical injury to a teacher
51 or to an employee of a public educational institution during
52 or as a result of the performance of his or her duty, he or
53 she causes physical injury to any person.
54 (6) With intent to cause physical injury to a health
55 care worker, including a nurse, physician, technician, or any
56 other person employed by or practicing at a hospital as
Page 2

other person employed by or practicing at a hospital as
