57 defined in Section 22-21-20; a county or district health
58 department; a long-term care facility; a physician's office,
59 clinic, or outpatient treatment facility during the course of
60 or as a result of the performance of the duties of the health
61 care worker or other person employed by or practicing at the
62 hospital; the county or district health department; any health
63 care facility owned or operated by the State of Alabama; the
64 long-term care facility; the physician's office, clinic, or
65 outpatient treatment facility; or a pharmacist, pharmacy
66 technician, pharmacy intern, pharmacy extern, or pharmacy
67 cashier; he or she causes physical injury to any person. This
68 subdivision shall apply to assaults on home health care
69 workers while they are in a private residence. This
70 subdivision shall not apply to assaults by patients who are
71 impaired by medication.
72 (7) For a purpose other than lawful medical or
73 therapeutic treatment, he or she intentionally causes stupor,
74 unconsciousness, or other physical or mental impairment or
75 injury to another person by administering to him or her,
76 without his or her consent, a drug, substance, or preparation
77 capable of producing the intended harm.
78 (8) With intent to cause physical injury to a
79 Department of Human Resources employee or any employee
80 performing social work, as defined in Section 34-30-1, during
81 or as a result of the performance of his or her duty, he or
82 she causes physical injury to any person.
83 (9) With intent to cause physical injury to a letter
84 carrier, as defined in Section 32-6-380, during or as a result
