87 (10) With intent to cause physical injury to a child,
88 as defined in Section 16-22A-3, located in an educational
89 environment, as defined in Section 16-22A-3, he or she: (i) is
90 at least 19 years of age; (ii) is not employed by or enrolled
91 in the entity associated with the educational environment, as
92 defined in Section 16-22A-3; and (iii) causes physical injury
93 to any person.
94 (b) Assault in the second degree is a Class C felony.
95 (c) For the purposes of this section, "utility worker"
96 means any person who is employed by an entity that owns,
97 operates, leases, or controls any plant, property, or facility
98 for the generation, transmission, manufacture, production,
99 supply, distribution, sale, storage, conveyance, delivery, or
100 furnishing to or for the public of electricity, natural or
101 manufactured gas, water, steam, sewage, or telephone service,
102 including two or more utilities rendering joint service."
103 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
104 1, 2026.
